com.here.mobility.sdk.core.geo

Class GeoBox

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.here.mobility.sdk.core.geo.GeoBox
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Parcelable

    public final class GeoBox
extends Object
implements Parcelable
    A "rectangle" on the planet, bounded by meridians and latitudes. GeoBoxes are immutable. The valid ranges of the meridians and latitudes are the same as in LatLng. The southern latitude must always be less than or equal to the northern latitude. The "western" meridian, however, can be greater than the "eastern" meridian, allowing geo-boxes to cross the ±180 longitude line.

      • getBounds

        public static GeoBox getBounds(HasLatLng loc1,
                               HasLatLng loc2,
                               double uncrossedLongitude)
        Returns the smallest bounding box of the two given locations that does not cross the given longitude line. Two coordinates on a sphere do not unambiguously define a smallest bounding box, because there are two such boxes - one that goes over the "front" of the sphere and ones over the "back". By specifying a meridian that the box should not cross, you can control which of the two boxes is returned.

      • getBounds

      • getBounds

        public static GeoBox getBounds(Collection<? extends HasLatLng> locations,
                               double uncrossedLongitude)
        Returns the smallest bounding box of the given locations that does not cross the given longitude line. This can be used to control which of the possible bounding boxes (there are as many as there are distinct longitudes among the points) will be returned. Note that if any of the location's longitudes equal the uncrossed longitude, the returned box will have its east value set to that longitude.
